Like stagecoaches, swinging saloon doors and Pony Express riders, there are many innovations of the Old West that have long faded from use and live on only in Western movies and history books.

But there are still a few frontier staples that were so effective and ahead of their time that they remain in use today. Take, for instance, the intimidating octagonal barrels commonly found on the repeating rifles of that period. These heavy-duty workhorses sported added mass and extra weight to aid in heat absorption, making them the forerunners to the bull barrels used on modern target and varmint rifles.

title: For Sale:  Buyer beware for SKS
postcontent:
I recently bought an SKS from an individual I found on Armslist, I am no way saying that Armslist is responsible for this happening. Upon taking said SKS to the range, I took three shots and ended up with this:
[URL=http://s1156.photobucket.com/user/piercerhb/media/IMG_20140701_155502_zpsc0a017c3.jpg.html][/URL]

To all future SKS buyers, please either take it to a gunsmith before buying or firing it, or at least take the rifle out of the stock and make sure there are no holes drilled into the rifle, mine had a hole drilled into the chamber and this caused my stock to snap in half, I almost got injured by this and I am now out $200 bucks. I just wanted to put this warning out there to prevent more people from getting screwed like I did. Thank you for reading.

I am told by fellow Mosin collectors it was made this way for snipers, so they would not be betrayed by a shiny rifle at night. As it is, the finish is extremely smooth to the touch, and very pretty. I have never seen any sniper have this finish before, nor any standard Mosin.


   I have yet to shoot this rifle, but the scope looks fairly easy to use, and the bolt cycles nicely. There is no rust I have found yet, but I have not taken it apart for a full cleaning yet.


Feel free to contact me anytime for more information. The price is firm. I also have several standard Mosin 91/30's, all in 'Excellent' Condition, if you prefer a battle rifle to a full-blown sniper.


Regards,

     Thomas

Swivel and band screws

Unknown:
Rear sight(have not removed to look for the marks, so as not to mess with adjustment)
